"Whether the candidates get the job depends first on their outward appearance, such as height, weight, facial features, etc."
Then come temperament and "inner qualities".
"Female Chengguan are like flower vases," he said, adding, "but beyond that, they have other duties."
Zheng Lihua, deputy head of the district's city administration, does not agree with this description,
but admitted that in China size requirements in job ads for both sexes are not uncommon.
