But people with disabilities or physical disfigurements need not apply.
"Unfortunately, we can't use lameness or hunches here," said Mr. Zheng.
“Your image would not be good.”
Liu Yi, who is patrolling Baoguang Square near a monastery, is 22, has apple rolls and a well-shaped mouth.
She didn’t feel sexist that so much importance was placed on her appearance.
"Do you think I look sexy in this uniform?" she asks with an ironic look.
Her colleague with the ditches, 21-year-old Xu Yang, commented, "We have the task of representing the image of the city."
According to them, they do not regret the short hiring, as they have more ambitious career plans than just scaring merchants through the alleys to prevent them from doing business.
